Republicans performed far better than expected in the battles for the Senate and the House. Meanwhile, depressed and angry Dems are having flashbacks to 2016.

More in Huddle 👇

https://t.co/feSsr5QNsK

name: politico
text:
Twitter slapped a warning label on a tweet by Ben Wikler, chair of the Democratic Party of Wisconsin, for prematurely claiming that Joe Biden had won the state as votes were still being counted
https://t.co/vgJUIlWDNN

name: politico
text:
Michigan, Pennsylvania and Wisconsin — and their 46 electoral votes — vaulted Donald Trump into the White House in 2016.

And once again, they're playing a decisive role in 2020. Here's where vote-counting stands in each of them.
https://t.co/m9RLEZJyff

name: politico
text: Wisconsin proved to be far more competitive than the Biden campaign — and polls— had projected, partly due to strong turnout in the state's rural counties. As of 11:13 a.m. ET, 95% of the expected vote has been counted. https://t.co/7E6ADdbxtf

name: politico
text:
In Michigan, 96% of the expected vote is in. The state's top elections official says Michigan's presidential results could be known by the end of the day.

Live results: https://t.co/3TVe9VDakn

https://t.co/FS9CjXFQJv

name: politico
text:
In Pennsylvania, a sizable amount of the expected votes in both Philadelphia and Allegheny County (the home of Pittsburgh) are still outstanding.

Live results: https://t.co/aXmNi1KqCb

name: politico
text:
If there’s any good news to be gleaned from this moment of election uncertainty, it’s consensus among researchers that (at least for now) foreign interference has been nowhere near as problematic as it was in 2016.

More in Morning Tech 👇
https://t.co/pwbEhas1sO https://t.co/9cIp345jFD

name: politico
text:
The pandemic and the rise of China are prompting a turn to government power to grow industries important to America’s security.

On Global Translations, @luizachsavage and @PoliticoRyan talk to the people trying to make industrial policy cool again. 
https://t.co/0u7NyPwSWN https://t.co/DUyNed1zJL

text:

name: politico
text: Donald Trump’s path to reelection has narrowed significantly after Joe Biden flipped Arizona on Wednesday and pulled into the lead in Wisconsin and Michigan https://t.co/LIithXre5S

name: politico
text: Trump could sill secure his reelection through the Great Lakes states in the upper Midwest, where final counts are hours, or even days, away  https://t.co/LIithXre5S
